  <main class="pt-32 pb-16 px-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-diwy mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
    <div class="space-y-4">

      <!-- FAQ Item Template -->
      <details class="group border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold text-diwy text-lg group-open:mb-2">How do you pronounce DIWY? What does it mean?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2">DIWY is pronounced <strong>"dee-wee"</strong>, like the word <strong>“kiwi.”</strong><br>
        It stands for <strong>Do It With You</strong>, because we believe financial planning should be a collaborative experience. You don’t have to do it all yourself, and you don’t have to hand everything over — we work <em>with</em> you, side by side.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold text-diwy text-lg group-open:mb-2">Do I have to move my money or open new accounts?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2"><strong>No.</strong> DIWY is an <strong>advice-only</strong> financial planning firm. That means we don’t manage your assets or require you to move accounts. You keep control of your money, and we provide clear, objective guidance to help you make better decisions.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold text-diwy text-lg group-open:mb-2">Do you sell products or earn commissions?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2"><strong>No.</strong> We don’t sell insurance, investments, or any financial products. We are <strong>fee-only fiduciaries</strong> — the only thing you pay for is <em>our time and advice</em>. No sales, no hidden agendas.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold text-diwy text-lg group-open:mb-2">What do you charge?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2">We offer a <strong>flat-fee, pay-as-you-go model</strong> starting at $500. You only pay for the time we spend together in meetings — not for work done behind the scenes. That means you’re in control of the pace, scope, and budget.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold text-diwy text-lg group-open:mb-2">Who do you work with?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2">We work with people from all walks of life — whether you’re just starting out, in a career transition, juggling family finances, or planning for retirement. We specialize in working with <strong>self-directed clients</strong> who want an expert partner to <strong>plan collaboratively</strong> — not take over.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold text-diwy text-lg group-open:mb-2">What if I just have a few quick questions?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2">That’s exactly what we’re here for. You can book a one-time session or schedule multiple meetings — it’s up to you. There’s no long-term contract or ongoing retainer unless you want one.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold text-diwy text-lg group-open:mb-2">Do you meet virtually?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2">Yes! We meet with clients <strong>virtually by phone or video</strong>, so you can get advice from anywhere — no need to travel or change your schedule.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold text-diwy text-lg group-open:mb-2">How do I get started?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2">It’s simple — just visit our <a href="https://calendly.com/alfaber/60minutemeeting" class="text-blue-600 underline hover:text-blue-800">scheduling page</a> to book a 60-minute meeting. You’ll choose a time that works for you and receive a short intake form so we can make the most of your session.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="group border rounded-lg p-4">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold text-diwy text-lg group-open:mb-2">What tools do you use?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2">We use a secure, intuitive planning platform that allows you to organize your financial life, track progress toward your goals, and store important documents. We also use screen sharing, interactive visuals, and other tools to keep our sessions clear, collaborative, and actionable.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
